This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it deals with the study of online human behavior and social interactions. It could also belong to the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE) as it discusses the development of better platforms and services. Other possible sub-categories include Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as the study of online behavior can have implications for security, Systems and Control (cs.SY) as the paper deals with the evolution of user actions over time, and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as it discusses the predictability of individual interactions.
